nate variant of the biblical name   Adah .  However, it has also been explained as a pet form of   Adele   and   Adelaide  , Germanic female names of which the first element is <i>adal</i> ‘noble’. It was borne by a 7th-century abbess of Saint-Julien-des-Prés at Le Mans."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Baroness Ada Florennes was born in 1063, in Rumigny, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France, her father, Godefroi IV de Rumigny Lord of Florennes and Rumigny, was 44 and her mother, Florennus, was 49. She married William Le Fleming before 1085, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1131, in Cambrai, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, at the age of 68, and was buried in France."},"et":{"1063–1131":"1063–1131","1059–1150":"1059–1150","1085–1154":"1085–1154","1020–1078":"1020–1078","1015–Female":"1015–Surnud","1015":"1015","1059":"1059","1078":"1078","1154":"1154","Aft 5 February 1078":"pärast 5. veebruari 1078","1131":"1131","1020":"1020","1063":"1063","before 1085":"enne 1085","1085":"1085","1150":"1150","England":"England","Rumigny, Ardennes, Champagne, France":"Rumigny, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa","Cambrai, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Cambrai, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa","Caernarvon Castle, Beckermet, Cumberland, England":"Beckermet, Cumberland, England"},"fi":{"1063–1131":"1063–1131","1059–1150":"1059–1150","1085–1154":"1085–1154","1020–1078":"1020–1078","1015–Female":"1015–Kuollut","1015":"1015","1059":"1059","1078":"1078","1154":"1154","Aft 5 February 1078":"5. helmikuuta 1078 jälkeen","1131":"1131","1020":"1020","1063":"1063","before 1085":"ennen vuotta 1085","1085":"1085","1150":"1150","England":"England","Rumigny, Ardennes, Champagne, France":"Rumigny, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, Ranska","Cambrai, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Cambrai, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Ranska","France":"Ranska","Caernarvon Castle, Beckermet, Cumberland, England":"Beckermet, Cumberland, England"},"